  <section id="challenges-affecting-snow-leopards" class="slider-slice_container paragraph-container">
    <section class="square-carousel " aria-labelledby="carousel-heading">
      <div class="article_wrapper square-carousel-heading-container">
                  <h3>
            Challenges affecting snow leopards
          </h3>
                      </div>

      <div class="splide">
        <div class="splide__track">
          <ul class="splide__list">
                                                                    <li class="splide__slide">
                <figure>
                  <img src="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_xs/public/2016-09/Large_WW214859.jpg?h=cac311d4&amp;itok=T0g4ZxUx"
                       srcset="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_xs/public/2016-09/Large_WW214859.jpg?h=cac311d4&amp;itok=T0g4ZxUx 320w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_s/public/2016-09/Large_WW214859.jpg?h=cac311d4&amp;itok=2EkFibzl 640w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_m_new/public/2016-09/Large_WW214859.jpg?h=cac311d4&amp;itok=TLghqysQ 768w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW214859.jpg?h=cac311d4&amp;itok=Sw7QE8NQ 1024w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW214859.jpg?h=cac311d4&amp;itok=Sw7QE8NQ 1200w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW214859.jpg?h=cac311d4&amp;itok=Sw7QE8NQ 1440w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW214859.jpg?h=cac311d4&amp;itok=Sw7QE8NQ 1536w"
                       alt=""
                       sizes="(max-width:320px) 100vw,
                       (max-width: 640px) 90vw,
                       (max-width: 1024px) 75vw,
                       (max-width:1440px) 50vw,
                       33vw"
                  />
                                      <div class="splide-copyright">© Staffan Widstrand 2004, All Rights Reserved</div>
                                    <figcaption>
                    <a href="#" class="show show-text">More <i class="show fa fa-arrow-circle-o-up"></i></a>
                    <a href="#" class="hide hide-text">Close <i class="hide fa fa-close"></i></a>

                                                                                  <h4>Loss of living space</h4>
                                        <div class="description-container">
                      <p>In many areas the snow leopard’s living space is being destroyed or broken up because of the activities of people – for instance grazing livestock.</p>

                                                                      <div class="find-out-more-container">
                          <a href="https://www.wwf.org.uk/what-we-do/protecting-our-natural-places">
                                                          Learn more
                                                        <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
                          </a>
                        </div>
                                          </div>
                  </figcaption>
                </figure>
              </li>
                                                                    <li class="splide__slide">
                <figure>
                  <img src="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_xs/public/2016-09/Large_WW215459.jpg?h=56d0ca2e&amp;itok=LMUGHNcD"
                       srcset="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_xs/public/2016-09/Large_WW215459.jpg?h=56d0ca2e&amp;itok=LMUGHNcD 320w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_s/public/2016-09/Large_WW215459.jpg?h=56d0ca2e&amp;itok=qK96PvPu 640w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_m_new/public/2016-09/Large_WW215459.jpg?h=56d0ca2e&amp;itok=9VRPildd 768w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW215459.jpg?h=56d0ca2e&amp;itok=RWrbQ7fE 1024w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW215459.jpg?h=56d0ca2e&amp;itok=RWrbQ7fE 1200w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW215459.jpg?h=56d0ca2e&amp;itok=RWrbQ7fE 1440w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW215459.jpg?h=56d0ca2e&amp;itok=RWrbQ7fE 1536w"
                       alt=""
                       sizes="(max-width:320px) 100vw,
                       (max-width: 640px) 90vw,
                       (max-width: 1024px) 75vw,
                       (max-width:1440px) 50vw,
                       33vw"
                  />
                                      <div class="splide-copyright">© WWF-Canon / Steve Morgan</div>
                                    <figcaption>
                    <a href="#" class="show show-text">More <i class="show fa fa-arrow-circle-o-up"></i></a>
                    <a href="#" class="hide hide-text">Close <i class="hide fa fa-close"></i></a>

                                                                                  <h4>Climate change</h4>
                                        <div class="description-container">
                      <p>Climate change is an emerging threat. As our planet becomes warmer, plants and animals that need colder temperatures may need to move higher up mountains or further north. This is likely to shift and shrink the snow leopard’s range.</p>

                                                                      <div class="find-out-more-container">
                          <a href="https://www.wwf.org.uk/what-we-do/climate-change-and-energy">
                                                          Learn more
                                                        <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
                          </a>
                        </div>
                                          </div>
                  </figcaption>
                </figure>
              </li>
                                                                    <li class="splide__slide">
                <figure>
                  <img src="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_xs/public/2016-09/Large_WW147400_0.jpg?h=78538de2&amp;itok=N-W72VGZ"
                       srcset="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_xs/public/2016-09/Large_WW147400_0.jpg?h=78538de2&amp;itok=N-W72VGZ 320w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_s/public/2016-09/Large_WW147400_0.jpg?h=78538de2&amp;itok=vMRq6Oe5 640w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_m_new/public/2016-09/Large_WW147400_0.jpg?h=78538de2&amp;itok=DoK9UX72 768w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW147400_0.jpg?h=78538de2&amp;itok=cpnXLNGe 1024w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW147400_0.jpg?h=78538de2&amp;itok=cpnXLNGe 1200w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW147400_0.jpg?h=78538de2&amp;itok=cpnXLNGe 1440w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW147400_0.jpg?h=78538de2&amp;itok=cpnXLNGe 1536w"
                       alt=""
                       sizes="(max-width:320px) 100vw,
                       (max-width: 640px) 90vw,
                       (max-width: 1024px) 75vw,
                       (max-width:1440px) 50vw,
                       33vw"
                  />
                                      <div class="splide-copyright">© James Morgan / WWF-US</div>
                                    <figcaption>
                    <a href="#" class="show show-text">More <i class="show fa fa-arrow-circle-o-up"></i></a>
                    <a href="#" class="hide hide-text">Close <i class="hide fa fa-close"></i></a>

                                                                                  <h4>Conflict with people</h4>
                                        <div class="description-container">
                      <p>Because their natural prey are also in decline, snow leopards sometimes eat local livestock, which can result in the farmers killing them in retaliation. This is now one of the biggest threats to snow leopards in parts of their range. &nbsp;</p>

                                                                      <div class="find-out-more-container">
                          <a href="https://www.wwf.org.uk/what-we-do/preventing-human-wildlife-conflict">
                                                          Learn more
                                                        <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
                          </a>
                        </div>
                                          </div>
                  </figcaption>
                </figure>
              </li>
                                                                    <li class="splide__slide">
                <figure>
                  <img src="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_xs/public/2016-09/Large_WW139473.jpg?h=2e5cdddf&amp;itok=Dpik0iGj"
                       srcset="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_xs/public/2016-09/Large_WW139473.jpg?h=2e5cdddf&amp;itok=Dpik0iGj 320w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_s/public/2016-09/Large_WW139473.jpg?h=2e5cdddf&amp;itok=80lkn2ab 640w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_m_new/public/2016-09/Large_WW139473.jpg?h=2e5cdddf&amp;itok=4MmsIH6l 768w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW139473.jpg?h=2e5cdddf&amp;itok=XresleaT 1024w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW139473.jpg?h=2e5cdddf&amp;itok=XresleaT 1200w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW139473.jpg?h=2e5cdddf&amp;itok=XresleaT 1440w,
                         https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/square_l/public/2016-09/Large_WW139473.jpg?h=2e5cdddf&amp;itok=XresleaT 1536w"
                       alt=""
                       sizes="(max-width:320px) 100vw,
                       (max-width: 640px) 90vw,
                       (max-width: 1024px) 75vw,
                       (max-width:1440px) 50vw,
                       33vw"
                  />
                                    <figcaption>
                    <a href="#" class="show show-text">More <i class="show fa fa-arrow-circle-o-up"></i></a>
                    <a href="#" class="hide hide-text">Close <i class="hide fa fa-close"></i></a>

                                                                                  <h4>Poaching and Illegal wildlife trade</h4>
                                        <div class="description-container">
                      <p>Despite their godlike local status, snow leopards are also poached for their fur and body parts. Their stunning coat is most in demand, but their bones are also sold, mainly for use in traditional Asian medicine.</p>

                                                                      <div class="find-out-more-container">
                          <a href="https://www.wwf.org.uk/what-we-do/stopping-illegal-wildlife-trade">
                                                          Learn more
                                                        <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
                          </a>
                        </div>
                                          </div>
                  </figcaption>
                </figure>
              </li>
                      </ul>
        </div>
